subSubSection.paragraph:
Additional description: female and male
. Clypeus with depth of ventral emargination 0.2–0.3 × median length of clypeus. Malar space distinctly or slightly narrower than facet of eye, without setae. Forewing with basal corner of cell 1M slightly acute. Hind wing of male with apex of cell 1A rather close to wing margin (
Fig. 4S
; fig. 2n in 
Hara & Shinohara, 2013
); section of marginal vein in cell Cu (arrowed in 
Fig. 4S
) separated from wing margin in posterior fourth. Mesoscutellum with only inconspicuous minute punctures (
Fig. 5L
). Mesoscutellar appendage mostly setose. Dorsum of abdomen not microsculptured, sometimes partly slightly microsculptured.
